cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically predicting future frame segmentation from monocular video. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses the task of predicting camera ego-motion, which falls under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of learnable sub-modules and recurrent neural networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also deals with semantic labeling, which is a sub-topic of natural language processing (cs.CL).
